You are rewriting the campaign wizard page and wiring the campaign dashboard to real backend data for an AI email outreach platform. Frontend is Next.js 16 at `/Users/tanishqsingh/Desktop/yash desktop files/projects/outreach-proj/frontend-v2/`.

## Context

The app is an AI email outreach platform. When a user creates a campaign, they go to `/campaign/[id]/wizard` which should be a **real-time chat interface** with an AI assistant. The AI asks questions about the campaign and extracts parameters. When the AI is done extracting params, the user clicks "Launch" which finalizes the session and starts processing.

The backend has:
- `GET /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/chat` → returns `{ session_id, status, chat_history, extracted_params }`
- `POST /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/chat` with `{ message }` → SSE stream of `{ type: "token", content: "..." }` and final `{ type: "done", extracted_params: {...} }`
- `PUT /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/sessions` with `{ extracted_params }` → finalizes session, starts processing

The frontend already has a typed API client at `src/lib/api.ts` with:
```typescript
getChatHistory(campaignId) → ChatHistoryResponse
sendChatMessage(campaignId, message) → AsyncGenerator<{type, content?, extracted_params?}>
// PUT sessions is missing - you need to add it to api.ts
```

`ChatHistoryResponse`:
```typescript
interface ChatHistoryResponse {
  session_id: string;
  status: string;
  chat_history: ChatMessage[];
  extracted_params: Record<string, unknown>;
}
interface ChatMessage {
  role: "assistant" | "user";
  content: string;
}
```

## What you must build

### 1. Add `finalizeSession` to `src/lib/api.ts`
Append this function to the existing api.ts:
```typescript
export async function finalizeSession(
  campaignId: string,
  extracted_params: Record<string, unknown>
): Promise<{ message: string; campaign_id: string }> {
  return apiFetch(`/api/v1/campaigns/${campaignId}/sessions`, {
    method: "PUT",
    body: JSON.stringify({ extracted_params }),
  });
}
```

### 2. REWRITE `src/app/campaign/[id]/wizard/page.tsx`
Replace the entire multi-step form wizard with a real chat UI. The current file is a multi-step form that doesn't connect to the backend.

The new wizard page should:

**Layout**: Use the existing `Sidebar` + `Topbar` shell. Two-column layout: left side is chat, right side shows extracted params.

**Chat UI requirements**:
1. On mount: call `getChatHistory(id)` to load existing messages (including the AI's first message set when campaign was created)
2. Display chat messages in a scrollable container:
   - Assistant messages: left-aligned, accent background
   - User messages: right-aligned, bg-1 background
3. Text input at the bottom + Send button (or Enter to send)
4. On send: add user message to UI immediately, call `sendChatMessage(id, message)` async generator, stream AI tokens into a growing assistant message bubble (update the message character by character as tokens arrive)
5. When `{ type: "done", extracted_params }` arrives: update the extracted params panel on the right
6. If `extracted_params` has enough data (has at least 2 keys), show a "Launch campaign →" button
7. "Launch campaign" calls `finalizeSession(id, extracted_params)` then navigates to `/campaign/${id}/processing`

**Extracted params panel** (right side):
- Shows key-value pairs from `extracted_params`
- Title: "Extracted parameters"
- If empty: show "Chat with the AI to build your campaign" hint text
- Keys formatted nicely (replace underscores with spaces, capitalize)

**Loading state**: Show spinner while loading chat history.

**Error state**: If backend returns error, show error message with retry button.

Here is the exact structure to follow (you implement the logic):
```tsx
"use client";
import React from "react";
import { useParams, useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import { Icon } from "@/components/ui/Icon";
import { Sidebar } from "@/components/layout/Sidebar";
import { Topbar } from "@/components/layout/Topbar";
import { getChatHistory, sendChatMessage, finalizeSession } from "@/lib/api";
import type { ChatMessage } from "@/types/index";

export default function WizardPage() {
  const { id } = useParams<{ id: string }>();
  const router = useRouter();
  // ... implement full chat UI
}
```

Key CSS classes from the app's design system:
- Container: `className="shell"`, inner: `className="main"`
- Buttons: `className="btn btn-primary btn-sm"`, `className="btn btn-ghost btn-sm"`
- Inputs: `className="field"`
- Colors: `var(--bg)`, `var(--bg-1)`, `var(--bg-2)`, `var(--fg)`, `var(--fg-2)`, `var(--fg-3)`, `var(--accent)`, `var(--accent-dim)`, `var(--border)`, `var(--border-strong)`
- Font: monospace via `var(--font-mono)`

Make the chat UI look polished and match the dark theme aesthetic.

### 3. Wire `src/app/campaign/[id]/dashboard/page.tsx` to real data
The current dashboard has hardcoded `ROWS` array with mock data. Replace it with real data from the backend.

The backend endpoints:
- `GET /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/outreach?page=1&limit=50` → returns `{ outreaches: OutreachDraft[], total, page, limit }`
- `GET /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/stats` → returns `CampaignStats`
- `PATCH /api/v1/campaigns/{id}/outreach/{outreach_id}` → approve/reject

`OutreachDraft`:
```typescript
interface OutreachDraft {
  id: string;
  contact: Contact;
  subject: string;
  body: string;
  draft_status: "pending" | "approved" | "rejected";
  status: "draft" | "queued" | "sent" | "failed";
}
interface Contact {
  company: string; person_name: string; email: string; title: string; source: string; bounce_risk: boolean;
}
interface CampaignStats {
  total_contacts: number; total_drafts: number; approved: number; queued: number; sent: number; opened: number; replied: number; bounced: number; failed: number;
}
```

The `listOutreach`, `getCampaignStats`, `updateOutreach` functions are already in `src/lib/api.ts`.

Changes needed to dashboard page:
1. Remove the hardcoded `ROWS` array
2. Add state: `outreaches`, `stats`, `loading`
3. On mount: fetch both `listOutreach(id)` and `getCampaignStats(id)` in parallel
4. Map `OutreachDraft` to the Row interface the table expects (company from contact.company, etc.)
5. The stats strip at top should use real `stats` data
6. The "Send" button should call `enqueueEmails(id, selected_outreach_ids)` (already in api.ts)
7. Keep all the existing UI components (table, drawer, send modal) - just replace mock data with real

The `Row` type used in the dashboard may need updating — map outreach fields to it.

## Files to read first
Read these before writing:
- `src/app/campaign/[id]/wizard/page.tsx` (current file to replace)
- `src/app/campaign/[id]/dashboard/page.tsx` (to update with real data)
- `src/lib/api.ts` (existing functions)
- `src/types/index.ts` (all type definitions)

## Rules
- The wizard page must connect to real backend — no mock data, no timeouts
- Auto-scroll chat to bottom when new messages arrive (useEffect on messages)
- The streaming must work: use `for await (const event of sendChatMessage(...))` in an async function
- After writing, run: `cd /Users/tanishqsingh/Desktop/yash\ desktop\ files/projects/outreach-proj/frontend-v2 && bun run build 2>&1 | tail -20`

Return: summary of every file changed and whether build passes.

